        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 3:58PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Prices Fork, or near Newport, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Christiansburg...
Radford...
Pembroke...
Newport...
Mountain Lake...
and Laurel Branch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
